<task id="034" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-B-05 Migrate matter-prefill action: populate outputSchema + node destination = form-prefill (NFR-07 binding regression)</title>
    <phase>Phase B — Schema-Aware Output</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>3-4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>030, 031</dependencies>
    <blocks>048</blocks>
    <tags>dataverse, seed, migration, integration-test</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>NFR-07 BINDING — pre-fill flow signatures + 45s timeout + `useAiPrefill` MUST remain UNCHANGED. Even though this is "data only", the matter-prefill flow is binding-sensitive; any regression breaks production wizard. FULL rigor required: code-review + adr-check at Step 9.5 + explicit before/after pre-fill regression test.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>B-G2</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Touches matter-prefill action row + matching playbook node — different rows from siblings 032/033/035. Pre-fill regression test runs in isolation against a test matter; no shared state.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Populate the new `outputSchema` field on the matter-prefill `sprk_analysisaction` row,
    and set the playbook node `destination = form-prefill`. This is one of TWO
    NFR-07-binding migrations (the other is project-prefill in task 035). The pre-fill
    flow signatures, the 45s timeout, and the `useAiPrefill` React hook MUST remain
    COMPLETELY UNCHANGED. Only the action's `outputSchema` data field is populated. The
    node's `destination = form-prefill` is the routing surface — but `form-prefill` is a
    no-op for the WIDGET (form-prefill output goes directly to wizard fields via
    `MatterPreFillService` + `IWorkspacePrefillAi`; it does NOT use
    `StructuredOutputStreamWidget`).

    **NFR-07 BINDING**: pre-fill hook signatures + 45s timeout + `useAiPrefill` UNCHANGED.
    Only the data field `outputSchema` is populated. Before/after pre-fill regression
    test REQUIRED. Inspect `IWorkspacePrefillAi`, `MatterPreFillService`, the
    `useAiPrefill` hook, and the wizard's pre-fill consumer; confirm all signatures are
    untouched. Run a full end-to-end pre-fill on a test matter BEFORE the migration; run
    the SAME end-to-end after; diff field-by-field. If ANY field changes value, behavior,
    or timing — STOP, ROLL BACK, and report immediately.

    Schema change escalation gate per CLAUDE.md Confirmation Triggers: this task modifies
    data on a binding-sensitive production action; user confirmation required at start
    of task. Migration script MUST be idempotent (guard GET → PATCH). BFF publish-size
    delta = 0 MB (no BFF code modified).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Deep familiarity with the pre-fill flow:
    `IWorkspacePrefillAi` PublicContract, `MatterPreFillService`, `findBestLookupMatch`,
    `AiFieldTag`, the 45s timeout, `Workspace:PreFillPlaybookId` config, the
    `useAiPrefill` React hook, the wizard `$choices`-constrained output contract. Capable
    of running a careful before/after regression test that proves NO change in behavior,
    signatures, or timing.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `sprk_analysisaction` row for the matter-prefill action has `sprk_outputschema`
    populated with a valid JSON Schema that exactly mirrors the existing
    `$choices`-constrained output the wizard consumes today. The playbook node has
    `destination = form-prefill`. Migration script committed + idempotent + applied to
    Spaarke Dev. A documented before/after pre-fill regression test proves NO change
    in: (a) `IWorkspacePrefillAi` signature; (b) `MatterPreFillService` behavior; (c)
    45s timeout enforcement; (d) `useAiPrefill` hook behavior; (e) per-field wizard
    output values; (f) end-to-end latency profile.
  </goal>

